OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWhen 15 rain-soaked        
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fmarchers made history in   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FIndia                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Pride parades in India today are       
OL,6, vibrant affairs, where thousands gather
OL,7, to express themselves and offer support
OL,8, to the queer community. But things were
OL,9, very different in 1999, when the       
OL,10, country's first Pride walk was         
OL,11, organised in the eastern state of West 
OL,12, Bengal. Journalist Sandip Roy revisits 
OL,13, the trailblazing event.                
OL,15,FOn 2 July 1999, Pawan Dhall, a queer   
OL,16,Frights activist in Kolkata city, was   
OL,17,Famong the 15 intrepid marchers to      
OL,18,Fparticipate in what was later called   
OL,19,Fthe first Pride walk in India.         
